{
  "_comment": "Example MCP server configuration for Claude Code",
  "_instructions": [
    "MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers extend Claude Code with external tools.",
    "Place this in .mcp.json at your project root, or in ~/.claude/.mcp.json for global config.",
    "Each server runs as a subprocess that Claude Code communicates with via stdio or HTTP."
  ],

  "mcpServers": {
    "code-search": {
      "_comment": "Trigram-based code search server (e.g., Zoekt)",
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/mcp-servers/code-search/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "SEARCH_INDEX_PATH": "/path/to/code-index",
        "MAX_RESULTS": "50"
      }
    },

    "web-fetch": {
      "_comment": "Fetch web pages as markdown for AI consumption",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@anthropic/mcp-web-fetch"],
      "env": {
        "USER_AGENT": "Claude-Code-Agent/1.0"
      }
    },

    "database-query": {
      "_comment": "Read-only database access for analysis",
      "command": "python3",
      "args": ["/path/to/mcp-servers/db-query/server.py"],
      "env": {
        "DATABASE_URL": "postgresql://readonly_user:${DB_PASSWORD}@localhost:5432/mydb",
        "MAX_ROWS": "1000",
        "TIMEOUT_SECONDS": "30"
      }
    },

    "kubernetes-ops": {
      "_comment": "Kubernetes cluster operations (read-only by default)",
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/mcp-servers/k8s-ops/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "KUBECONFIG": "${HOME}/.kube/config",
        "ALLOWED_NAMESPACES": "default,staging",
        "READ_ONLY": "true"
      }
    },

    "memory-store": {
      "_comment": "Persistent memory/notes across sessions",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@anthropic/mcp-memory"],
      "env": {
        "MEMORY_DIR": "${HOME}/.claude-memory"
      }
    },

    "github-tools": {
      "_comment": "GitHub API integration for issues, PRs, and code review",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@anthropic/mcp-github"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  },

  "_settings_example": {
    "_comment": "Companion settings.json (place in ~/.claude/settings.json)",
    "permissions": {
      "allow": [
        "Bash(git *)",
        "Bash(gh *)",
        "Bash(npm test *)",
        "Bash(npx jest *)",
        "Read",
        "Write",
        "Edit",
        "Glob",
        "Grep",
        "mcp__code-search__search",
        "mcp__web-fetch__fetch",
        "mcp__memory-store__*"
      ],
      "deny": [
        "Bash(rm -rf /)",
        "Bash(curl * | sh)",
        "mcp__database-query__write"
      ]
    },

    "hooks": {
      "PreToolUse": [
        {
          "matcher": "Edit",
          "hooks": [
            {
              "type": "command",
              "command": "echo 'Editing file: will be reviewed'"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "PostToolUse": [
        {
          "matcher": "Bash",
          "hooks": [
            {
              "type": "command",
              "command": "echo 'Command completed'"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

    "env": {
      "PROJECT_ROOT": "/path/to/your/project",
      "NODE_ENV": "development"
    }
  },

  "_architecture_notes": [
    "",
    "MCP Server Architecture:",
    "",
    "  Claude Code <--stdio--> MCP Server Process",
    "       |                       |",
    "       |--- tool calls ------->|--- external service",
    "       |<-- tool results ------|<-- (API, DB, search, etc.)",
    "",
    "Key Points:",
    "- Each MCP server is a separate process",
    "- Communication via stdin/stdout (stdio transport) or HTTP (SSE transport)",
    "- Servers declare tools, resources, and prompts",
    "- Claude Code auto-discovers available tools from connected servers",
    "- Environment variables support ${VAR} substitution from shell env",
    "",
    "Security Best Practices:",
    "- Never hardcode API keys -- use environment variable references",
    "- Use read-only access by default for database and cluster servers",
    "- Limit allowed namespaces/databases/paths to what's needed",
    "- Set timeouts to prevent runaway queries",
    "- Use the permissions.deny list to block dangerous operations",
    ""
  ]
}
